      "content": "it wasnt formatting though. i checked everything like ten times. the rejection came within hours. they didnt even send a formal reason, just a generic \"not suitable for our scope\" email. i have friends in the field and they're saying the same thing—that certain labs are gatekeeping the new math because if i'm right, their entire funding for the next decade disappears. it feels intentional. how can a journal reject a whole new framework in two hours without even a preliminary look?",
